        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:225:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/356/438",
        "text": [
          "۳۵۶. وَقِيلَ لَهُ (عليه ‏السلام) لَوْ سُدَّ عَلَى رَجُلٍ بَابُ بَيْتِهِ، وَتُرِكَ فِيهِ مِنْ أَيْنَ كَانَ يَأْتِيهِ رِزْقُهُ؟ فَقَالَ (عليه السلام):"
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "356. It was said to Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him: If a man is left in his house and the door is closed, from where will his livelihood reach him. And he replied:"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1915,
        "local_index": 2,
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:225:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/356/439",
        "text": [
          "مِنْ حَيْثُ يَأْتِيهِ أَجَلُهُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "From whatever way his death reaches him. [1]"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
